# app/templates/

This folder contains HTML templates rendered by Flask using Jinja.

## Key idea
Templates define the page structure. They can reuse shared layout via template inheritance.

- `base.html` usually contains the shared shell (head, nav, footer)
- Page templates (e.g. `index.html`, `about.html`) typically `extend` the base and fill blocks

## Jinja basics
- `{{ ... }}` prints a value into the HTML (e.g. `{{ title }}`)
- `{% ... %}` runs template logic (e.g. inheritance, loops, conditionals)

Example pattern:

```html
{% extends "base.html" %}
{% block content %}
  <h1>Page Title</h1>
{% endblock %}


What belongs here:

-Page templates
-Shared layout templates (base.html)
-Reusable partials (optional later, e.g. partials/nav.html)

What does NOT belong here:

-Database code
-Business logic
-JS scripts (those go in app/static/js/)